Subject: Re: [racket-bug] all/14967: Readline does not pick up user keybindings from ~/.inputrc
Date: Tue, 10 Feb 2015 10:29:36 -0800

 Thanks for the suggestions to both of you. After a bit of searching online for the differences between libedit and deadline, I discovered that libedit uses ~/.editrc and that it has different command syntax ("man 5 editrcâ€). To test, add:
 
 	bind "^[i" ed-prev-history # Meta-i
 
 to ~/.editrc, and M-i should cycle back in history.
 
 Davor
 
